original_title: Grateful Dead: New Jersey Half-Step Uptown Toodleloo - Live at The Capitol Theater
overview: 1977 saw The Grateful Dead at the height of their powers. The new songs were solid, the band was playing better than ever and the bootleg recordings from that year prove it. This video captures the second and third nights of a three-night stand at Passaic, New Jersey's Capitol Theater. Highlights include: "Estimated Prophet", "Eyes Of The World", "Sugar Magnolia", "Promised Land", "Loser" and many more.
title: Grateful Dead: New Jersey Half-Step Uptown Toodleloo - Live at The Capitol Theater
